quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  29,15,"But We saved him and the companions of the Ark, and We made the Ark a sign for all people"
  29,16,"And We also saved Abraham. Behold, he said to his people, “Serve God, and be conscious of Him. That will be best for you, if you understand"
  29,17,"“For you worship idols besides God, and you create falsehood. The things that you worship besides God has no power to give you sustenance. So seek sustenance from God, serve Him, and be grateful to Him. To Him will be your return"
  29,18,"“And if you reject the message, so did generations before you, and the duty of the messenger is only to preach publicly and clearly.”"
  29,19,Do they not see how God originates creation then repeats it? Truly that is easy for God
  29,20,"Say, “Travel through the earth and see how God originated creation, as will God produce a later creation, for God has power over all things"
  29,21,"“He punishes whom He pleases, and He grants mercy to whom He pleases, and toward Him are you turned"
  29,22,"“Neither on earth nor in heaven will you be able to flee from, or sabotage his plan, nor have you besides God, any protector or helper.”"
  29,23,"Those who reject the signs of God and the meeting with Him in the hereafter, and those who despair of My mercy, they will suffer a most terrible penalty"